rComments: One of the best professors I've ever had! She's organized and her teaching style is easy to follow and engage with. Went to see her regarding an essay and she's really helpful. As a person, she's so sweet and nice, I would take any class of hers.

Been doing well throughout the whole course, until the last two assignments. Stable 80's throughout the course. Given a low 70 and asked for a regrade and got a 60. Completely unjustifiable and out of character. Judged paper by being petty and misuse of power. Do not take her class if you want to pass. She is super ditsy and tech-challenged
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: She taught me Video Games and shes an absolute gem. She's there to answer any question of yours and even willing to talk about the career behind the course. Very inspirational and interesting professor, would definitely take again.

Siobhan is approachable, curious & open-minded. Her teaching style embraces the co-creation of knowledge & integrates of self-exploration. She is passionate about community development & connecting her students to organizations, the arts & people that can facilitate learning. She always makes herself available -office hours, class time and online.

Very passionate about the material and goes in depth. You must attend lectures and take notes (or know someone who does). You don't necessarily need to read the books; lec notes enough. The assignments are easy, but the TA does mark hard. If you need an extension, you can have a week no questions asked the first time around & sometimes second time.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Absolutely amazing professor who really connects with her students.  Lectures don't feel long because the subject matter is so fun and interesting to discuss.  No tests in this class, but a few papers.  My favourite course that I've taken yet.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read']

rComments: She's really awesome and understanding of mental/health issues. I loved her class and would be pleased to have her again!

She is not approachable at all, very rude actually. Lectures are long & useless. I tried to take notes but there was nothing good that she said. When she discussed the reading list novels in detail, she was unclear & very vague on a lot of points. Aside from that, her TA was not accessible & is a completely outrageous marker.  Would not recommend.

She teaches a bunch of classes and then tell you she's said something when she hasn't. I think she gets mixed up. She got some interesting points, but her slides had a lot of typos and she  is far from approachable and friendly. In fact, she's pretty much not very nice. This makes asking questions pretty hard. I was so excited. I'd avoid her.

I've taken several classes with Professor O'Flynn and I loved all of them. She goes into a lot of depth with the novels she teaches, and she seems really passionate about her work which comes through in her lectures. She also integrates social media platforms like Tumblr and Pinterest into her assignments which I thought was really cool.

I really liked her as a professor. We read some interesting children's lit for the course, and she provided some really interesting insights. Her lectures can get boring because she tends to talk non-stop for hours. As long as you have read the books you should be fine since essay and exams questions are open-ended.

Great class! Prof. O'Flynn was a wonderful instructor who engaged every student in the class. There was a lot of work (lots of readings and critical reflections) but her marking was extremely fair and she was always available for help. She went above and beyond for her students and even gave us lifts to our class outings. Phenomenal experience.

Siobhan, the humble, outgoing, and approachable prof students are fortunate to have. She relates to students, is compassionate, and above all knows what she is talking about. I would recommend any of her courses, especially her seminar. She packs a lot in but you leave gaining more than just a good grade! Just ask and she will help as best she can!

Had the astounding ability to make a class I was very interested the most profoundly boring/awful class i have taken. She does not utilize online resources, also does not specify where you should be in the readings. Found her lectures very scattered and bland, and quite frankly - boring.
One of the worst profs. Not helpful at all. Unclear on ideas and her TA's mark too hard for a 2nd year course. Expectations are 2 sided, says one things but marks it a different way.
Really enthusiastic.  Dont take the 3 hour night class, as you may lose interest, but if I'd had her during a better time I'd have remained very interested.

Boring. She keeps talking about a "shift" of perspective as though such a thing were inherently interesting. She doesn't go into any depth. She lavishes praise on her handsome pet and ignores the others. She's also very critical of different points of view than her own. She thinks she's a smart, "cool" prof, but she's just a poser.

Her teaching is below average because she repeatedly draws from a convenient set of postmodern and postcolonial stock responses. She avoids the more difficult task of engaging a work according to its own principles of design. I suggested this and suffered the consequences of her ideological wrath. She is passive agressive. Beware.
I think shes a great prof who teaches well and keeps the class engaged.
one word: HORRIBLE!
wonderful, engaging, fair marker. excellent prof!
COOL

She was my favorite english prof, and I was an english major :S. honestly her course is good, and she marks fairly. while the lectures are that great and sometimes boring, you leave her class wellrounded with a wide range of readings involved. I liked it and was overall a good first year experience.

She is very enthusiastic about the course and is extremely knowledgeable. A good down to earth person and knows the content inside and out. This is refreshing in a teacher! If you donâ€™t understand anything she is more than happy to help out. Glad she is teaching at OCAD.

No boring, but thourough. And she really seems interested in the material she is teaching. Maybe the classes can get boring beacuse she lets students talk so much and some of them have a tendency to ramble or repeat. I would highly recommend her classes.
3 words...Boring Boring Boring!  Anyone else notice she yawns while talking during her lectures.  I guess she's not all that bad since she can multi-task.

At times lectures felt a little boring (though the 3 hour evening time slot could be the culprit). Though considering the time aspect, lectures were still informative (don't be silly and skip!) and really only dragged the last 30-40 minutes ;)
nice teacher, great for first year courses when trying to get the hang of university.  Talks slowly, it's easy to take notes in her class.
